<span class=title> RANT - WTF is up with all these train jumper nuts?</span><hr size=1> What kind of person thinks it is cool, funny, or even beneficial to their cause to commit further acts of terrorism just because the world is more aware and perhaps more fearful of them since the attack on the World Trade Centers and Washington DC.<br><br>I am sick of being sent home from work because of Bomb Threats in the skyscraper I work in or nearby skyscrapers. <br><br>I can't think of a single instance of a bomb threat accomplishing anything other than to further separate the threatening organization from the sypathies of the rest of the world.<br><br>I can't think of a single act of terrorism that has earned any organization the respect of the world.<br><br>Actually I can't think of a single act of terrorism that actually produced terror that lasted more than a few a weeks. The physical damage done by terrorists will last a long time but when we see it and remember we wont remember fear, we will remember anger and resolve.<br><br>Terrorism does not work. It never has it never will. These dumb train jumping nuts...<br><br>Anyway, it needs to stop.<br><br>G  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usalenie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salenie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/13/01 9:17:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=134.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RANT - WTF is up with all these train jumper nuts?</span><hr size=1> I have a theory!<br><br>Terrorism doesn't work, as Ghie noted above.  It doesn't persuade.  It doesn't enlist.  What it generally does is get people very pissed off at the perpetrators.  Now what does this resemble?<br><br>Trolls never persuade people with their outlandish arguements.  It doesn't garner people to their side.  The most extreme cases are usually from anonymous or one-shot sources (like terrorists hiding in caves, avoiding claiming responsibility).  It does, however, garner the troller a LOT of attention.<br><br>Maybe this is a paralel.  And no, the paralel is NOT NOT NOT that trolls and terrorists are the same type of person.  Please do NOT put that into my mouth.<br><br>But maybe, just maybe, the impetus for the action is similar.  Maybe the feeling of being separated from main stream society, of feeling like no one notices you, of having this pain or desire that no one else seems to care about, cause anti-social and extreme action--and action guaranteed to get a reaction.<br><br>Or maybe not.  I'm not a troller in general, and I'm definitely not a terrorist, so maybe the motivation is completely different.  It is a theory though. <p>Salenie Silkweaver<BR>Proud Member of <a href=" http://www.clanbattleaxe.com">Clan Battle Axe</a> </p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showPrevMessage?topicID=134.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showNextMessage?topicID=134.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=134.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.emailToFriend?topicID=134.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=